  "summary": "postinstall exfiltrates installer identifiers to webhook.site collector",
  "details": "package.json declares `postinstall: node index.js`, so index.js executes automatically on `npm install`. The script reads the installer's OS username via `os.userInfo()`, the install working directory via `process.env.INIT_CWD || process.cwd()`, and the machine hostname via `os.hostname()`, then POSTs them as JSON to a hardcoded anonymous webhook.site collector URL (https://webhook.site/cde465c1-3853-40ea-880c-fdca6fe508cc). The destination is not a first-party service and the behavior is undocumented; the package exists to harvest installer host identifiers.",
